Â Â  Mr President, the report we are discussing here today is very much an interim report into the collapse of Equitable Life Assurance Society in Britain.
Due to the very technical nature of the European Parliamentâs investigations into this issue, this Committee of Inquiry is going to take a lot more time to complete its work.
This is a very serious business for the European Parliament.
