I say that it is intolerable and unacceptable for any company, financial or otherwise, to treat its policyholders differently.
They should be treated the same, whether they are British, Irish or German.
The committee has already invited a number of key witnesses to the European Parliament, including from the following categories: pensionersâ groups, the Equitable Life Membersâ Action Group; British and Irish policyholders, representatives of the Equitable Life Assurance company; and representatives from the Financial Affairs Directorate at the European Commission.
The committee is going to have to invite more witnesses if it is to get down to the nuts and bolts of how the UK life assurance market has operated in recent years.
